<li id="cite_note-40"><b><a href="#cite_ref-40" title="">^</a></b> <span class="languageicon" style="font-size:0.95em; font-weight:bold; color:#555;">(German)</span> <a href="http://www.villiton.ch/vollspektrumlicht.php" class="external free" title="http://www.villiton.ch/vollspektrumlicht.php" rel="nofollow">http://www.villiton.ch/vollspektrumlicht.php</a></li>
</ol>
<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Light_tube&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<p><a name="Overview" id="Overview"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Light_tube&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Overview">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Overview</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Light Tubes on "Potsdamer Platz" are made by Heliobus AG Switzerland <a href="http://www.heliobus.com" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.heliobus.com" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li>"Smart Lighting for a Smart House" (an overview over daylighting, listing also light pipes) - <a href="http://www.smarthouse.duke.edu/downloads/smart_lighting_noor.ppt" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.smarthouse.duke.edu/downloads/smart_lighting_noor.ppt" rel="nofollow">[2]</a> ,<a href="http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:hfq4UoFXUMIJ:www.smarthouse.duke.edu/downloads/smart_lighting_noor.ppt+sunlight+courtyard+heliostat&amp;hl=de&amp;gl=de&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=1" class="external text" title="http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:hfq4UoFXUMIJ:www.smarthouse.duke.edu/downloads/smart_lighting_noor.ppt+sunlight+courtyard+heliostat&amp;hl=de&amp;gl=de&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=1" rel="nofollow">HTML</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.fsec.ucf.edu/BLDG/ACTIVE/fenestration/solLighting/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.fsec.ucf.edu/BLDG/ACTIVE/fenestration/solLighting/index.htm" rel="nofollow">Solar lighting</a> and <a href="http://www.fsec.ucf.edu/BLDG/ACTIVE/fenestration/solLighting/piped.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.fsec.ucf.edu/BLDG/ACTIVE/fenestration/solLighting/piped.htm" rel="nofollow">Illumination of Buildings using Light Pipes</a>, Florida Solar Energy Center (at the University of Central Florida)</li>
<li><a href="http://etheses.nottingham.ac.uk/archive/00000026/01/Thesis_-_Joel_Callow.pdf" class="external text" title="http://etheses.nottingham.ac.uk/archive/00000026/01/Thesis_-_Joel_Callow.pdf" rel="nofollow">Daylighting Using Tubular Light Guide Systems</a> (thesis)</li>
<li><span class="languageicon" style="font-size:0.95em; font-weight:bold; color:#555;">(German)</span> an overview over light guidance - <a href="http://bine.info/pdf/infoplus/pro0100systematik.pdf" class="external text" title="http://bine.info/pdf/infoplus/pro0100systematik.pdf" rel="nofollow">PDF</a>, <a href="http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:yWQqhEXs2doJ:bine.info/pdf/infoplus/pro0100systematik.pdf+%22light+pipe%22+3M+solar&amp;hl=de&amp;gl=de&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=4" class="external text" title="http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:yWQqhEXs2doJ:bine.info/pdf/infoplus/pro0100systematik.pdf+%22light+pipe%22+3M+solar&amp;hl=de&amp;gl=de&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=4" rel="nofollow">HTML</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:p75yHX4tgw4J:www.iaeel.org/iaeel/archive/right_light_proceedings/Proceedings_body/BOK4/RL4shao.pdf+%22light+pipe%22+3M+solar&amp;hl=de&amp;gl=de&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=20" class="external text" title="http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:p75yHX4tgw4J:www.iaeel.org/iaeel/archive/right_light_proceedings/Proceedings_body/BOK4/RL4shao.pdf+%22light+pipe%22+3M+solar&amp;hl=de&amp;gl=de&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=20" rel="nofollow">"A Study of Performance of Light Pipes Under Cloudy and Sunny Conditions in the UK"</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.world-science.net/othernews/050310_suntubefrm.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.world-science.net/othernews/050310_suntubefrm.htm" rel="nofollow">"Sunlight in a tube", World Science, 2005</a></li>
<li>A series of <a href="http://www.sunpipe.co.uk/technical/index.php" class="external text" title="http://www.sunpipe.co.uk/technical/index.php" rel="nofollow">technical reference</a> information pages from the UK, referring to installation and mounting information</li>
<li><a href="http://ncr101.montana.edu/Light1994Conf/6_6_Kneipp/Kneipp%20text.htm" class="external text" title="http://ncr101.montana.edu/Light1994Conf/6_6_Kneipp/Kneipp%20text.htm" rel="nofollow">"Use of prismatic films to control light distribution", K. G. Kneipp, International Lighting in Controlled Environments Workshop, T.W.Tibbitts (editor), 1994, NASA-CP-95-3309</a> (with an overview on the piping of light)</li>
<li><span class="languageicon" style="font-size:0.95em; font-weight:bold; color:#555;">(German)</span> Alexander Rosemann: Hohllichtleiter für Tageslichtnutzung. Pflaum Verlag, München 2002. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/3790508624" class="internal">ISBN 3-7905-0862-4</a></li>
<li>"A Design Tool for Predicting the Performances of Light Pipes" Jenkins et al<a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=MImg&amp;_imagekey=B6V2V-4DVTGNF-3-1&amp;_cdi=5712&amp;_user=273788&amp;_orig=search&amp;_coverDate=05%2F01%2F2005&amp;_sk=999629994&amp;view=c&amp;_alid=448611134&amp;_rdoc=34&amp;wchp=dGLbVzz-zSkzk&amp;md5=580292344ec5f606ba4c271817fa2ca2&amp;ie=/sdarticle.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=MImg&amp;_imagekey=B6V2V-4DVTGNF-3-1&amp;_cdi=5712&amp;_user=273788&amp;_orig=search&amp;_coverDate=05%2F01%2F2005&amp;_sk=999629994&amp;view=c&amp;_alid=448611134&amp;_rdoc=34&amp;wchp=dGLbVzz-zSkzk&amp;md5=580292344ec5f606ba4c271817fa2ca2&amp;ie=/sdarticle.pdf" rel="nofollow">link title</a></li>
<li>UK based <a href="http://www.sunpipe.co.uk/sunpipe/index.php" class="external text" title="http://www.sunpipe.co.uk/sunpipe/index.php" rel="nofollow">Monodraught <i>SunPipe</i></a> (and www.sunpipe.info) with extensive technical and reference information</li>
<li>UK based (<a href="http://www.glidevale.com/downloads/Sunscoop%20Tubular%20Rooflights.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.glidevale.com/downloads/Sunscoop%20Tubular%20Rooflights.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.glidevale.com/downloads/Sunscoop%20Tubular%20Rooflights.pdf</a>) and www.glidevail.com with extensive technical and reference information</li>
<li><a href="http://www.monodraught.co.uk" class="external text" title="http://www.monodraught.co.uk" rel="nofollow">Monodraught</a> SunPipe - the UK's largest and most successful vendor of Light Tube products and solutions.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.humphrey-house.com/search/label/suntunnel" class="external text" title="http://www.humphrey-house.com/search/label/suntunnel" rel="nofollow">Case study installing light tubes in an older residential bungalow</a></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Other_approaches_to_sunlight_capture_and_transmission" id="Other_approaches_to_sunlight_capture_and_transmission"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Light_tube&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Other approaches to sunlight capture and transmission">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Other approaches to sunlight capture and transmission</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://blog.modernmechanix.com/2006/06/01/depthscrapers-defy-earthquakes/#more-715" class="external text" title="http://blog.modernmechanix.com/2006/06/01/depthscrapers-defy-earthquakes/#more-715" rel="nofollow">the Japanese approach of "depthscraper"</a>&#160;: a rotating mirror planned to throw sunlight deep down into a courtyard.</li>
<li>Courtyard facade with heliostats in Karl-Scharnagl-Ring Street in Munich, Germany - <a href="http://www.learn.londonmet.ac.uk/packages/synthlight/handbook/doc/cs3_munich.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.learn.londonmet.ac.uk/packages/synthlight/handbook/doc/cs3_munich.pdf" rel="nofollow">PDF</a>, <a href="http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:4hD3uwS11LAJ:www.learn.londonmet.ac.uk/packages/synthlight/handbook/doc/cs3_munich.pdf+sunlight+courtyard+heliostat&amp;hl=de&amp;gl=de&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=2" class="external text" title="http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:4hD3uwS11LAJ:www.learn.londonmet.ac.uk/packages/synthlight/handbook/doc/cs3_munich.pdf+sunlight+courtyard+heliostat&amp;hl=de&amp;gl=de&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=2" rel="nofollow">HTML</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.tribecatrib.com/newsjune05/mirrors.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.tribecatrib.com/newsjune05/mirrors.htm" rel="nofollow">Heliostats in New York City, USA</a></li>
<li>Description, among other topics, of the <a href="http://ncr101.montana.edu/Light1994Conf/6_6_Kneipp/Kneipp%20text.htm" class="external text" title="http://ncr101.montana.edu/Light1994Conf/6_6_Kneipp/Kneipp%20text.htm" rel="nofollow">3M Solar Optical Products Daylighting Panel</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.freepatentsonline.com/4761716.html" class="external text" title="http://www.freepatentsonline.com/4761716.html" rel="nofollow">US patent 4761716</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.freepatentsonline.com/6502950.html" class="external text" title="http://www.freepatentsonline.com/6502950.html" rel="nofollow">US patent 6502950</a></li>
</ul>


